{% doc %}
  @prompt
    Rebuild the existing "Dossier Reviews" block (blocks/ai_gen_block_198ec01.liquid) with full interactivity. Keep the exact same visual design: EB Garamond serif for headings, Inter sans-serif for body, black/white color palette, luxury editorial aesthetic inspired by dossier.co.
    
    Fix and add the following:
    
    1. WRITE A REVIEW MODAL: The "Write a Review" button must open a full-screen overlay modal containing a review submission form with fields: Star rating selector (1–5, clickable stars), Review title (text input), Review body (textarea), Author name (text input), and a Submit button. The modal should have a close (×) button and close on overlay click. On submit, show a thank-you message (no actual backend needed — just UI feedback).
    
    2. QUESTIONS TAB: The tabs ("Reviews" and "Questions") must actually toggle between two panels. The Reviews panel shows the existing hardcoded review cards. The Questions panel shows a Q&A list (3 hardcoded Q&A pairs editable via block settings: question text + answer text). The active tab should be underlined/bold, inactive tab should be muted. Add a text input + submit button at the bottom of the Questions panel so users can submit a question (UI only, no backend).
    
    3. SORT DROPDOWN: The "Sort" select (Highest Rating / Most Recent) must actually re-order the visible review cards in the DOM when changed.
    
    Keep all existing block schema settings (average_rating, review_count, rating bars, 3 reviews with title/text/author/date/verified/response, brand_name, CTA button, desktop_width_percent, section_padding, background_color, title_size). Add 3 new Q&A pair settings to the schema (question_1, answer_1, question_2, answer_2, question_3, answer_3).
    
    The modal and tab switching must work without any external libraries — vanilla JS only.
{% enddoc %}
{% assign ai_gen_id = block.id | replace: '_', '' | downcase %}

{% style %}
  .ai-dossier-reviews-{{ ai_gen_id }} {
    display: block;
    width: {{ block.settings.desktop_width_percent }}%;
    max-width: 100%;
    padding: {{ block.settings.section_padding }}px 0;
    background-color: {{ block.settings.background_color }};
  }

